- [ ] Public
- [ ] Check "Add README"
- [ ] Click "Create repository"

### 1b. Upload Files
- [ ] In repository, click "Add file" â†’ "Upload files"
- [ ] Drag ALL files from `quicklinks-complete` folder
- [ ] Make sure folders are preserved (public/, public/css/)
- [ ] Click "Commit changes"

### 1c. Verify Upload
- [ ] You should see: server.js, package.json, public folder, .env.example, README.md
- [ ] Inside public/: index.html, login.html, signup.html, dashboard.html, admin.html
- [ ] Inside public/css/: auth.css

âœ… **Files are on GitHub!**

---

## Step 2: Deploy to Railway (5 minutes)

### 2a. Connect Railway
- [ ] Go to railway.app
- [ ] Click "Login with GitHub"
- [ ] Authorize Railway

### 2b. Deploy
- [ ] Click "New Project"
- [ ] Click "Deploy from GitHub repo"
- [ ] Find and select your `quicklinks` repository
- [ ] Click "Deploy Now"
- [ ] Wait 2-3 minutes (watch the logs!)

### 2c. Get URL
- [ ] Click "Settings" tab
- [ ] Scroll to "Domains"
- [ ] Click "Generate Domain"
- [ ] **Copy your URL:** `________________.up.railway.app`

âœ… **App is deployed!**

---

## Step 3: Configure Environment (5 minutes)

### 3a. Add Variables
In Railway, click "Variables" tab, then add these one by one:

```
PORT = 3000
```

```
SESSION_SECRET = make_this_a_long_random_string_abc123xyz789
```

```
ADMIN_EMAIL = youremail@gmail.com
```

```
ADMIN_PASSWORD = YourSecurePassword123!
```

```
BASE_URL = https://your-railway-url-here.up.railway.app
```

### 3b. Redeploy
- [ ] Click "Deployments" tab
- [ ] Click "Deploy" button
- [ ] Wait 1 minute

âœ… **App is configured!**

---

## Step 4: Test Everything (10 minutes)

### 4a. Test Landing Page
- [ ] Open your Railway URL
- [ ] Should see purple gradient page
- [ ] Click "Start Free Trial"

### 4b. Test Sign Up
- [ ] Fill in: Name, Email, Password
- [ ] Click "Start Free Trial"
- [ ] Should redirect to dashboard

### 4c. Test Creating Link
- [ ] Enter a URL (like https://google.com)
- [ ] Click "Shorten"
- [ ] Should see shortened URL
- [ ] Copy and open in new tab
- [ ] Should redirect to original URL

### 4d. Test Admin Panel
- [ ] Logout (button in top right)
- [ ] Go to /login
- [ ] Login with ADMIN credentials (from env variables)
- [ ] Should see Admin Dashboard
- [ ] Check if your test user shows up

âœ… **Everything works!**

